    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4963" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κᾱλός</span></b> , comp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καλλίων, κάλλιον</span>, nom. pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">καλλίονες</span>, sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κάλλιστος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">beautiful, fair;</span> sometimes
          figuratively, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">λιμήν, ἄνεμος, ζ 263</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 14.253</span></i>; met., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">fine,
            well, proper</span>, only neut. in Homer, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κᾱλὸν εἰπεῖν, κᾱλὰ ἀγορεύειν, κᾱλόν ἐστί τινι</span>.—Adv.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κᾱλόν, κᾱλά, καλῶς, Θ 400</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 2.63</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
